It's not as spicy as most Indian restaurants which is good for the American palet. If you prefer your food to be spicy spicy, just let them know.<//review>

<username>Christine Keil<//username><userid>111403436066076962662</userid><Date>1617769375779</Date><Review>They're the BEST!
My yorkie fur baby had acquired a weird cough and obviously wasn't feeling well. I was visiting from out of town, called and as a new client was able to get a appointment that same day.
The staff was prompt, courteous, polite and professional. With covid I had to wait in my car as my pup was taken inside, but I could tell he was in good hands.
A few minutes later a man came to my vehicle. It was the Vet who came to speak in person, not just a voice over the phone. He explained my pups diagnosis in terms I could understand, as well as the treatment options.
My pup received TOP NOTCH treatment and I felt I was treated with legitimate concern for his well-being.
All in all, he's better and although I live over an hr from their office, the service & care they provide is WELL WORTH the drive!<//Review><pictures>None<//pictures></record>

The renovated apartments are nice (not all are renovated, though) and Alameda is just lovely, but the property management company for this apartment complex is the worst I've dealt with in 10+ years of renting.

But things got much worse with COVID, as they barricaded themselves in their office and refused to answer the phones or emails. The package locker room situation turned into complete mayhem and packages were going missing, but they insisted this was because "residents weren't picking up their package" rather than acknowledging they didn't have nearly enough lockers for a place so big (the same thing would happen during the holidays). I am very sympathetic to the fact that they needed to close the office and all amenities to keep everyone safe and of course agree with that decision, but they never so much as acknowledged that we had 1.5 years of not being able to access the pool and gym, and they made themselves completely unavailable the entire duration of the pandemic.

<review>Despite all the reviews, I decided to take a look at Summer House after unsuccessful attempts in finding affordable rentals in surrounding neighborhoods. I had lived in Alameda before AND took a look at Summer House 3 years prior. Now, I'm a resident here. I have to say that the new management has changed this place for the better. Now that construction is complete, the grounds are gorgeous with water fountains all around, a gigantic swimming pool and beautiful plants and flowers.  The groundskeepers should be given full credit, as I see them outside everyday working on keeping the place clean and attractive (*reviews have been given about the trash and furniture around the dumpsters, which is accurate still, however, this is at the fault of the residents, not the property managers). The ordinary apartments are comparable to their going rates, so if you are looking for something plain to get you through the year, this is a great spot. They come with a double sink, dishwasher, electric stove, microwave, carpeted rooms, and easy cable hookup. So far we've had to call maintenance twice in the 3 months that we've been here. Though some appliances were not working properly when we moved in, the maintenance people were there on time and fixed our problems right away... no questions asked. Be careful for the "water fee" which is divided among the complex as a whole and attached to your monthly rent. There is ample parking but the car gates are not secure. Plenty of kids here who play in the complex when school is out. We live with a 10 year-old so he made friends right away. Last note, it can get a little noisy since the walls are pretty thin. I would suggest sticking with a top floor.< /review><Pictures>None< /Pictures>< response>

<user_name>Jeff Scott< /user_name>< user_id>
107265274637859422193< /user_id>
< Review>
It was a bad omen when I went to the bank for a cashier's check for rent and deposit, and the teller told me I should tear it up find a new place if I hadn't signed anything yet.  These have been my negative experiences in the one year I have lived here:

1. My roommate and I voiced concern over parking on the tour.  Our guide said, "The 3 bedroom apartments come with 2 spaces."  This is an outright lie. The excuse: "Oh, sorry, he is new here."

2. We were told the prices of the apartments are all reflected on the website.  We applied for our apartment based on website listing, and then the contract was for $200 more per month.  Their excuse was, "Sometimes there's a significant delay between the website updates and actual rent changes, especially during the summer when there are a lot of moves."

3. After signing a lease for $200 more than expected and one fewer parking space, a new blank lease appeared in our email  a month later asking for even more money.  They said there was an error, and we weren't being charged enough.  They didn't push it after we pointed out this was blatantly illegal, but they still act like they're doing us a huge favor and we're just trying to scheme them out of cash.

4. There is a significant amount of noise at night.  I was particularly peeved one night when a car with a custom engine and very loud after stock muffler was parked below my window at 1:30 AM just revving the engine over and over again.  Then the guy left the doors open on both sides and BLASTED his stereo.  I was going to call security, but when I looked again, I saw that it was the security guard.  I had to be at work 5 hours later.

5. Management is in cahoots with some local towing company, and they call them immediately if anything is amiss.  If you need to unload groceries because you don't have enough parking spots that come with the apartment, you're gambling if it will be there when you return, even if it's only 10 min.

6. People like to dig through the dumpster below my bedroom window on a daily basis, and they can be rather loud at times, too.

7. There are loud children everywhere.  Make sure your apartment isn't next to the parking lot or the playground.

8. You are next to 2 schools, which is convenient if you have kids, but a pain around 8AM and 3PM.

9. There's a creepy old guy in the complex across the street who just walks up and down the sidewalk and calls police for people who are parked illegally, even if you tell him you just need to run a bag of groceries upstairs before you hunt for parking elsewhere.

Basically, I should have listened to my bank teller.  I'm moving in a week, and I can't wait.<//Review>

I really liked living here. Here are the pros and cons:
Pros:
- Management office: People in the management office are very nice and helpful. I did not deal with all of them (they look very nice though), but I usually talk to Britnie, she is very very nice girl and very helpful. Always optimistic :)
- Price: Apartment price was very nice especially if u work in SF, though they require very good credit, and relatively high income to be able to live there
- Maintenance: They respond very quickly, usually less than 24 hours
- Facilities: Swimming pool, Gym, playground for kids, barbecue area
- Security: Place has gates and security guards at night.
- unit: has microwave and dishwasher
- Commute: bus station is 5 mins walk. 25 minutes Bus to SF, 5 mins to Oakland.

Cons:
- Washers are very good, but dryers were not that great. However, I knew that they will have pretty new washers/dryers on January 2016
- Sometimes, you hear people's footsteps above you, but its okay for me.
- Carpet in my apartment was not that new.<//Review>

<review>Went here because it was the closest place to my current Construction job
I have a non roster gun, being from AZ, anf in wasn't expecting much.  The kid, Because i know he was younger then me,  was cool and rwspectful when asking my name and number in case i wanted ro wait in my car for my turn in the store. Upon going upstairs i asked a gentleman. Because i have no idea who he was, ca about getting a holster for my h&k p30l. He informed me that they have one fir a p30 but since the bottom was open it might fit.  He then asked me if i had my sidearm. When i told him i had it in my car he told me ti make sure it was unloaded and cleared snd bring it in ti check the fit.  It fit.  He then proceeded to instruct me on the installation of the holster on the various attachments to make drawing more comfortable.

I am satisfied beyond belief.  Especially considering all the negative reviews.  These people were honest and helpful.< /review>< Rate>

I guess I am not a dental hypochondriac.Ok, maybe I have a slight case of dentophobia combined with trypanophobia. < review>
Ambiance :

Music was painfully loud and Im used to loud . They had a mariachi which I love but their speakers were blasting  to try to cover the music from their small bar in the next room. The bar was louder than any night club and it was just a very uncomfortable experience.  I walked out with a headache.

Food:

Mediocre .  They serves in big plates that are mainly 95% rice and beans.  The food is nothing  special and overpriced.  We had Shirmp al mojo de ajo and  it was undercooked and they used garlic seasoning instead of real garlic (8 small shrimps. I counted them). We ordered salad instead of rice and beans and don't have a single homemade dressing. The spicy  salsa was basically canned chipotle  chillies with some seasoning.  The bacon wrapped shrimp was okay... bacon was a little burned . The taquitos were okay and enchilada was just okay. Margaritas tasted like a lemonade kool-aid.

This place has so much potential the place it's really nice and  they have good menu but they lack  good chef and good management.</review>

< Review>
The best Mexican food. The lunch specials are cheap and very generous. Carnitas on Mondays only.

Since the interior of the building is domed, it must have been made with steel re-enforced concrete.

Concave ceilings aren't good for amplified music and loud crowds. So acoustics is bad and cell data service is weak.

When I eat there and there is live music, I eat in the patio. I get the same great service.< /Review>
